				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: some misguided chanters calling for ae and swarm kite nerfs<a name="55051"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 4 04 7:47 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Something I will point out is that there are plenty of bards who believe that swarm-kiting should be nerfed. I have been an advocate of vastly reducing the range of our charm songs for a very long time now and remain in favour of this approach. If this had been done for PoP we might have actually had a usable charm song for grouping bards!
<br />

<br />
It is also fair to say that mudflation has caused the huge problems that charms generate in the current game. Mobs have to be created with massive dps in order to challenge players, which in turn become the next generation of charmed pets. From the enchanter perspective this has been both a blessing and a curse. A blessing in that they are somewhat overpowered when they can bring the full force of a CoD pet to bear; a curse because in content where charm is not possible they are horribly underpowered.
<br />

<br />
I'd love to say I had the answer to this but alas I do not. I also do not want to become a mobile charming platform but that is also a possibility for the future of our class. Alot depends upon precisely the EQ devs decide to do in the next couple of expansions, but if overhaste remains capped, and with the overabundance of mana regen in the game, what precisely do you think bards are going to be doing in OoW and beyond? Especially if we get given (say) a lvl 70 charm song...
<br />

<br />
