				<td colspan="2"><span>Ive got news for you guys... Swarm kiting is already nerfed (kinda). Here is my point.
<br />
You can do well swarmkiting in the 50s with the bewitching buvaria song. Infact I went all 10 levels (with the exception of several LDONs) running in circles in nadox doing it. But once you hit 60 or so you get much less xp and makes it not worth the time, you get better xp in a pop group (though not nearly as good loot).
<br />

<br />
At 64 we get an upgrade..but it is not very useful considering it will only work on mobs up level 57. Again you will do better in a xp group.
<br />

<br />
Now with OOM coming out there has been a lot of talk about our new charm ( we will be getting another one). But the nerf is built into our charm. It has a max range of 40 so you will not be able to swarm kite..at all.. on purpose. People hate swarm kiting, which really ticks me off. Even a lot of the bards on The Concert Hall have posted how it is over powered. I guess after level 63 or so we should just resign ourselves to LONG BORING RAIDS. We are good for little else at that level.</span></td>
